History: -year-old female with history of increased lower extremity edema and dyspnea.
Findings: Frontal and lateral views of the chest were obtained. There are small-to-moderate bilateral pleural effusions with overlying atelectasis. Mild-to-moderate interstitial edema is also seen. Impression: Small-to-moderate bilateral pleural effusions with overlying atelectasis along with interstitial edema consistent with fluid overload.
